<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38168a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38168a">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38168a"> 168(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Sahu = spirit</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Next we see Ani kneeling in adoration before Osiris, and he says, &ldquo;Behold, I am in thy presence, O Lord of Amenti. There is no sin in my body. I have not uttered a lie knowingly. (I have) no duplicity. Grant that I may be like the favoured (or rewarded) ones who are in thy train.&rdquo; Under favour of Osiris Ani then became a <mark><i>sahu</i> <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> or &ldquo;spirit-body,&rdquo;</mark> and in this form passed into the Kingdom of Osiris. <small> E.A. Wallis Budge, <a name="BOD2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BOD2"><cite title="source">The Book of the Dead</cite></a> (1920) 30</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
